## Relationship Design

The model is built around **one-to-many relationships** from dimensions to fact tables.

### Main opportunity relationships
- Accounts[AccountSeq] -> Opportunities[AccountSeq]
- Products[ProductSeq] -> Opportunities[ProductSeq]
- Campaigns[CampaignSeq] or Campaign Name -> Opportunities[CampaignSeq] / Campaign Name
- Owners[SystemUserSeq] -> Opportunities[SystemUserSeq]
- Opportunity Calendar[Date] -> Opportunities[CloseDate] or opportunity date field

### Main case relationships
- Accounts[AccountSeq] -> Cases[AccountSeq]
- Products[ProductSeq] -> Cases[ProductSeq]
- Owners[SystemUserSeq] -> Cases[SystemUserSeq]
- Case Calendar[Date] -> Cases[Case Created On]

### Supporting relationship
- Industries -> Accounts

This relationship structure allows dimensions such as account, product, owner, and industry to filter fact tables in a natural and business-friendly way.

